Note:
Runa Advanced Standard Library: AST Manipulation Module

Provides advanced, production-grade Abstract Syntax Tree (AST) manipulation for metaprogramming, code analysis, and transformation. Supports robust construction, traversal, transformation, pattern matching, rewriting, annotation, validation, diffing, and merging. All code and comments follow Runa conventions.
:End Note

Note: AST Types and Interfaces
Type ASTNode is Dictionary with:
    node_type as String
    value as Any
    children as List[ASTNode]
    position as Position
    annotations as List[Annotation]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type Position is Dictionary with:
    line as Integer
    column as Integer
    offset as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type Annotation is Dictionary with:
    annotation_type as String
    value as Any
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Note: Core AST Manipulation Functions
Process called "create_ast_node" that takes node_type as String and value as Any and children as List[ASTNode] and position as Position returns ASTNode:
    Return ASTNode with:
        node_type as node_type
        value as value
        children as children
        position as position
        annotations as list containing
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "traverse_ast" that takes node as ASTNode and visitor as Function returns None:
    visitor with node as node
    For each child in node.children:
        traverse_ast with node as child and visitor as visitor

Process called "transform_ast" that takes node as ASTNode and transformer as Function returns ASTNode:
    Let new_node be transformer with node as node
    Let new_children be list containing
    For each child in new_node.children:
        Add transform_ast with node as child and transformer as transformer to new_children
    Set new_node.children to new_children
    Return new_node

Process called "match_ast_pattern" that takes node as ASTNode and pattern as ASTPattern returns Boolean:
    If node.node_type is not pattern.pattern_type:
        Return false
    If pattern.value is not None and node.value is not pattern.value:
        Return false
    If length of node.children is not length of pattern.children:
        Return false
    For i from 0 to length of node.children minus 1:
        If not match_ast_pattern with node as node.children[i] and pattern as pattern.children[i]:
            Return false
    Return true

Process called "rewrite_ast" that takes node as ASTNode and rules as List[RewriteRule] returns ASTNode:
    For each rule in rules:
        If match_ast_pattern with node as node and pattern as rule.pattern:
            Return rule.replacement
    Let new_children be list containing
    For each child in node.children:
        Add rewrite_ast with node as child and rules as rules to new_children
    Set node.children to new_children
    Return node

Process called "annotate_ast_node" that takes node as ASTNode and annotation as Annotation returns ASTNode:
    Add annotation to node.annotations
    Return node

Process called "validate_ast" that takes node as ASTNode returns Boolean:
    If node.node_type is None or node.children is None:
        Return false
    For each child in node.children:
        If not validate_ast with node as child:
            Return false
    Return true

Process called "diff_ast" that takes node1 as ASTNode and node2 as ASTNode returns ASTDiff:
    Let differences as list containing
    If node1.node_type is not node2.node_type or node1.value is not node2.value:
        Add ASTDifference with diff_type as "type_or_value", node1 as node1, node2 as node2, description as "Node type or value differs", metadata as dictionary containing to differences
    If length of node1.children is not length of node2.children:
        Add ASTDifference with diff_type as "children_count", node1 as node1, node2 as node2, description as "Children count differs", metadata as dictionary containing to differences
    For i from 0 to min(length of node1.children, length of node2.children) minus 1:
        Let child_diff as diff_ast with node1 as node1.children[i] and node2 as node2.children[i]
        Add all child_diff.differences to differences
    Return ASTDiff with:
        differences as differences
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "merge_ast" that takes base as ASTNode and other as ASTNode returns ASTNode:
    Let merged as ASTNode be create_ast_node with node_type as base.node_type, value as base.value, children as base.children plus other.children, position as base.position
    Set merged.metadata to base.metadata merged with other.metadata
    Return merged

Type ASTPattern is Dictionary with:
    pattern_type as String
    value as Any
    children as List[ASTPattern]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type RewriteRule is Dictionary with:
    rule_id as String
    pattern as ASTPattern
    replacement as ASTNode
    conditions as List[String]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type ASTDiff is Dictionary with:
    differences as List[ASTDifference]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type ASTDifference is Dictionary with:
    diff_type as String
    node1 as ASTNode
    node2 as ASTNode
    description as String
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] 